This feature allows to define the reading and interpretation properties of a catalog to be used in a Data Transformation project.

The functionality is useful, for example, if you want to define the type of character encoding to be used to interpret a source file to be imported and used as a catalog.

## Creating a new Catalog data field
- Open the Catalog resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

- If no data fields have been created yet, click **ADD COLUMN**.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Enter the required parameters:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Field**

**Description**

**Name**

Enter the name of the new column.

**Add another**

Select this option if you want to add another column after this one, without going back to the main screen.

- Click **ADD **to confirm. The new column is now visible in the main table; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

To create additional data fields, see [Adding a column](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-catalog-configuring-the-data-structure#creating-a-new-catalog-data-field) below.

For more information on the available actions, see [Managing the Catalog data structure](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-catalog-configuring-the-data-structure#managing-the-catalog-data) below

> Note

For more information on how to import an existing Catalog structure, see: [DT3 Catalog - Global Actions.](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-catalog-global-actions)

### Editing a column
- Move your mouse over the column name; the ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon appears.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to display the context menu.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the required action:

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Rename**

Rename the column.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Set as primary**

Set the column type to "Primary". The ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon is displayed next to the column name; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

A primary column contains values that uniquely identify the rows, therefore duplicate values are not allowed.

The name of a primary column cannot contain blank spaces. The system will automatically replace any blank spaces with an "_" (underscore) character.

> Tip

When a column is set as primary, select![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Set as non-primary**) from the menu to remove the assignment.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Duplicate**

Duplicate the column.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Delete**

Delete the column.

> Warning

No confirmation is required. This action cannot be undone.

### Adding a data row
- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add row**). The system adds a new row to the catalog and enables the text field of the first column of the catalog; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Double-click on the field corresponding to a column to enter the required value; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click anywhere outside of the field to save the value.

> Tip

To edit the value of a catalog record, double-click on the corresponding field and enter the required value.

## Searching the catalog
The **Search **field displayed in the top-right allows to search for a specific value in the catalog records.

Start typing the search string, the system automatically displays the rows containing a matching value; for example:
